content:

If travelling onto Goulburn, or other Opal enabled station along the Southern Highlands Line, you should not tap off when transferring from Coach to an Intercity train but instead tap off at your destination station.

Booking is not required for Opal customers on this route.

Allow extra travel time and use the Trip Planner for alternative transport options, including trains, buses or walking.

urlText: Pyrmont & CBD bus diversions for Runaway Sydney Half Marathon
content:
On Sunday 5 May buses to and from the city will be diverting and using different stops while roads are closed in the Sydney CBD and Pyrmont for the Runaway Sydney Half Marathon.
 
From 5am to 9.30am services to the city will divert via the Druitt St off-ramp and drop off at Market St Stand F (2000140). The stop on Sussex St after King St (2000228) will be missed. Services leaving the city will run as normal.
 
Passengers should allow extra travel time and check signs at bus stops for alternative stop locations. Visit the Runaway Sydney Half Marathon event page for more transport details.

urlText: Circular Quay diversions for Runaway Sydney Half Marathon
content:
On Sunday 5 May buses to and from the city will be diverting and using different stops while roads are closed in the Sydney CBD for the Runaway Sydney Half Marathon.
 
From 4am to 9.30am buses that usually run to and from Circular Quay will start and end trips at Martin Place due to event closures on Phillip St.
Services to the city will end trips at Martin Place Elizabeth St Stand C. Services leaving the city will start trips from Martin Place Elizabeth St Stand E (2000283).
 
Continue on foot or change for light rail services to travel between Martin Place and Circular Quay during this time. Trains are not operating to Circular Quay due to trackwork.
 
Passengers should allow extra travel time and check signs at bus stops for alternative stop locations. Visit the Runaway Sydney Half Marathon event page for more transport details.
